# 1. 旅立ちの前に

Kohane & An: ————♪ ————♪
Akito & Toya: ——————...♪
Toya: (I like the energy they're producing.)
Toya: (I can tell that they're excited just based on the way they're singing.)
Toya: (We may not be shouting it out loud, but we're all looking forward to leaping feet-first into a brand new world.)
Toya: ♪————————————!
Miku: Very nice. I really like the way they're raising the heat towards the end.
Rin: Yeah! I can't keep my body still from all this excitement!
KAITO: Everyone must be looking forward to tomorrow very much.
An: We set off for the United States tomorrow!
Akito: Yeah. What do you think the event Taiga's gonna be in will be like?
Kohane: It's probably going to be a lot different from the festivals that are held in Japan, right?
Toya: We'll want to learn as much as we can while we're over there, including that.
Luka: Hey, learning about events is great and all, but you should also try to do some sightseeing and get some shopping in while you're over there!
Akito: Hey, we're not going as tourists.
Toya: He's right. Yes, this trip overlaps with one of our long holidays, but we're also taking a few days off from school...
MEIKO: Oh, really?
Kohane: Yes, we all promised to go over what we missed and do whatever homework was assigned once we get home.
Rin: Yikes! That sounds really rough!
Akito: But it should be worth the trouble.
An: Exactly! It's not every day that we get to go overseas to see an event like this!
An: But I'm also a bit annoyed...
Miku: Annoyed? Why's that?
An: Because Uncle Taiga is paying for our trip. He even booked the hotel we're staying at and stuff.
Akito: Now that you mention it, their manager is supposed to chaperone us around, right?
Len: Wait, really?!
Rin: That's awesome! Why do you find that annoying?
An: Hmm... Uncle Taiga said it's only right of him to do, since he's the one who invited us...
An: And sure, he did, but we can't be dependent on him forever, you know?
An: I mean, we're in a race to see who's gonna stand on top of the world first, right?
Rin & Len: *Gasp*
Akito: Right... Especially with Ken and Taiga back as a team.
An: Exactly. It's like we're nowhere near the same level as them right now...
An: Which is why I'm a little annoyed by all this! It's like we're being told, “Here, I'm giving you a chance, so make the most of it.”
Kohane: Even after RAD BLAST, we were given a lot of help.
Akito: Yeah...
An: That's why I wanna grow so much during this trip that we're gonna make their eyes pop out!
An: And once we've made it big, we're gonna pay back every last cent!
Toya: Yes... You're very right. We'll grow, set out into the world and then give back all that they've given us.
Kohane: Yeah!
Len: Oh, you guys! You're going to New York during this trip, right?
Len: When you're there, can we pop out from time to time to see what it's like?
Akito: Hm? Yeah. Like always, just be careful you don't get seen.
Len: Woohoo! I've been hoping you'd say that ever since Toya told me all about your guys' trip!
Len: New York's a big place with lots of cool stuff, right?
Toya: Yes. It's one of the biggest cities in the world, and a gathering place for musicians of all kinds to make new music together.
Toya: And not only is it one of the entertainment capitals of the world, it also holds great influence in the fields of politics, economics and fashion.
Rin: Wow! Then, I'm also gonna tag along!
KAITO: I'd like to see it as well. New York is supposed to be a place of pilgrimage for DJs.
Luka: Oh, I'm very interested in seeing the neighborhood with all the graffiti I saw in that one magazine!
Miku: This may get out of hand quickly if we don't decide who's going to see what beforehand...
MEIKO: I agree... Why don't we decide by playing rock paper scissors a little later?
Toya: (I've gone overseas in the past, but that was mostly to see Dad's concerts and some traditional music festivals. Nevertheless, what I heard was beautiful and so different from what I'm used to experiencing normally...)
Toya: (As such, I'm very excited about the music we're going to encounter on this trip.)
Toya: (Also...)
Slade: So, we'll be waiting for you in the States!
Toya: (Is it just me, or did they know that we'd be visiting the United States soon...?)
Toya: (Many questions still remain... But we need to deal with what's in front of us right now.)
Toya: I have my passport, plane ticket and wallet... Which should just leave that plug adapter.
Toya: (My clothes and toiletries are all already packed.)
Toya: (Now I just need to get the carry-on bag where I'll be storing my valuables sorted and...)
Toya: Hm? A message? From who...?
Toya: ...!
